90, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Alice de Draffen Heiress of Draffen was born in 1201, in Ayrshire, Scotland. She married Hugh de Crawford before 1220, in Ayrshire, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1273, in her hometown, at the age of 72, and was buried in Scotland."},"et":{"1201–1273":"1201–1273","1190–1255":"1190–1255","1220–1297":"1220–1297","1222–Female":"1222–Surnud","21 September 1255":"21. september 1255","1190":"1190","1201":"1201","before 1220":"enne 1220","1222":"1222","1255":"1255","1220":"1220","1297":"1297","1273":"1273","1746":"1746","Loudoun, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Loudoun, Ayrshire, Scotland","Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1201–1273":"1201–1273","1190–1255":"1190–1255","1220–1297":"1220–1297","1222–Female":"1222–Kuollut","21 September 1255":"21. syyskuuta 1255","1190":"1190","1201":"1201","before 1220":"ennen vuotta 1220","1222":"1222","1255":"1255","1220":"1220","1297":"1297","1273":"1273","1746":"1746","Loudoun, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Loudoun, Ayrshire, Scotland","Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Scotl